[SN]TITLE[SN]
Euro 2016 countdown: Mark Hughes' scissor kick helps Wales beat Spain 3-0 in 1985

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Wales claimed an historic 3-0 victory over Euro 1984 runners-up Spain in Wrexham in 1985.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Media playback is not supported on this device
Ian Rush opened the scoring at the Racecourse with a first half tap-in before strike partner Mark Hughes' memorable scissor-kick goal sent the fans into raptures.
Legendary striker Rush sealed the comfortable win over the giants of world football but Wales failed to qualify for the 1986 World Cup.
